	       		<img alt='' src='http://0.gravatar.com/avatar/41069796aba12fda45269582fd6b8f0c?s=50&amp;d=http%3A%2F%2F0.gravatar.com%2Favatar%2Fad516503a11cd5ca435acc9bb6523536%3Fs%3D50&amp;r=X' class='avatar avatar-50 photo' height='50' width='50' />	   				   			<p>I&#8217;ve spent a ridiculous amount of time in the past twelve hours or so (I noticed you because of a random tweet of mine you favorited yesterday) reading, researching, absorbing, reblogging, RTing, bookmarking, etc. a lot of your work. This is far from the first piece to elicit an emotional response from me, but it&#8217;s the first that caused me to pause in the midst of reading so I could get hold of my sympathy and general upset before finishing the article. I can&#8217;t *not* comment. Your hurt (even though it&#8217;s years past) hit me on a visceral level that continues to ache.</p>
<p>No one is perfect or infallible or incapable of misreading or not noticing another person&#8217;s reactions, so it&#8217;s not my place to vilify the other people who were involved. I can&#8217;t even guarantee I wouldn&#8217;t make the same mistake (though I certainly hope I wouldn&#8217;t), as I&#8217;m regrettably human. But I hurt for you as I read this. Not as a dominant woman (who gets to live through her own consequences of not fitting the patriarchal, heteronormative, socialized-gender-norms rulebook), but simply as a fellow human being. I&#8217;m so very sorry for the hurt this caused you and the marks it left.</p>
